- Nagios is an open-source monitoring and alerting tool designed to oversee IT infrastructure components like servers, networks, applications, and services. 
- It was designed to run on the Linux operating system and can monitor devices running Linux, Windows etc.
- Helps to ensure the availability, performance, and security of critical systems.
- It offers flexibility with both command-line and web-based interfaces, allowing administrators to monitor systems efficiently.
- Nagios can monitor memory use, disk use and microprocessor load, network protocols, currently running processes and log files.
- Port no: 80, 443














